<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Intro</div>

<div class=itemtext>Mega Man 2 introduced a lot of the conventions that would be used in most of the Mega Man series, like 8 robots, E-Tanks, a variety of utility items, and the robot teleporter room.  It also introducced some of the most famous Mega Man bosses and weapons, such as Metal Man/Metal Blade and Wood Man/Leaf Shield.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Story</div>

<div class=itemtext>MM2 probably has the simplest storyline of the entire series.  Dr. Wily has built 8 robots of his own to counter Mega Man, and has returned for revenge and another world takeover.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Unique Features</div>

<div class=itemtext>Most of the changes made in Mega Man 2 really became part of the series in general.  MM2 is realy, basically, the most basic example of a Mega Man game.  I can think of 2 differences, though.  Instead of Rush, Mega Man gets around on 3 lifts called "Items."  The most unique feature of MM2 is an adjustable difficulty setting.  In difficult mode, Mega Man's shots do only half as much damage, rounded up, against bosses as they do in normal mode, and a few enemies take more hits.  Difficult mode uses the same settings as the Japanese version of MM2.  The normal mode in the English version was added because Capcom thought the game would be too difficult for U.S. players.<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Robots</div>

<div class=itemtext><a href=mm2robots.txt>Official Enemy Names List</a><br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

