<td VALIGN=TOP bgcolor=ffffff class=itemtable>
<font face=Arial size=-1 color=black><div class=titlebar>Vulnerability Loop</div>

<div class=itemtext>This is one of 4 original-series games that has a non-loop pattern.  The Crash Bomb is not the vulnerability of any particular boss, although it is quite powerful against several of them, and the Metal Blade is the vulnerability of Bubble Man, Flash Man, and Metal Man himself, who is also vulnerable to the Quick Boomerang.
<p>Metal -> Metal -> Flash -> Quick -> Metal -> Bubble -> Heat -> Wood -> Air -> Crash<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Damage Data</div>

<div class=itemtext><a href=mm2-data.html>Data For Mega Man & Robot Masters</a><br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Beginner's Level Orders</div>

<div class=itemtext>You'll need to fight 2 Robot Masters with the plasma cannon with this level order, but they're both fairly easy, and you'll get the Quick Boomerang and Item-2 faster.  The downside is that you won't have the Leaf Shield for the unlimited 1-up trick in Air Man's stage.
<p>Air -> Flash -> Quick -> Metal -> Bubble -> Heat -> Wood -> Crash
<p>This level order starts with Metal Man, and gives you the proper Master Weapon for all following bosses, while giving you the Air Shooter before entering the jumper-filled stages of Flash Man and Quick Man (see its weapon description for the reason).  However, you won't have Item-2 for Heat Man's stage.
<p>Metal -> Bubble -> Heat -> Wood -> Air -> Flash -> Quick -> Crash<br><br></div><div class=titlebar>Advanced Level Order</div>

<div class=itemtext>If you're planning to use the plasma cannon against most or all of the bosses, this level order wil keep you equipped with the best weapons possible for each level.
<p>Metal -> Wood -> Air -> Flash -> Quick -> Crash -> Heat -> Bubble<br><br></div></font></td></tr></table>

